Text.SourceString: Um…yes?
I haven’t seen you around here before.//Are you new?
It’s hard to get people to bring their own shopping bags.//So it’s probably a good thing <NPCName>Sam</> stopped giving out free paper bags.
Hopefully, we’ll all eventually remember, and bringing your own bag will be the new normal.//<portrait=happy>Ah, I see you have a backpack! You’ve got the idea, <PlayerName>$player</>.
It’s hard to get people to bring their own shopping bags.//So it’s probably a good thing <NPCName>Sam</> stopped giving out free paper bags.
Hopefully, we’ll all eventually remember, and bringing your own bag will be the new normal.//<portrait=happy>Ah, I see you have a backpack! You’ve got the idea, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Seems like Dad’s been complaining about the recycling area more lately.//I don’t go to that part of the island, so I have no idea what’s going on with it.
But I don’t think it’s that bad.//Everybody takes care of it, and it looks pretty clean from a distance.//<portrait=sad>But what do I know?
What’s up with people calling the recycling area the dumpster?//<portrait=annoyed>I guess it’s not wrong. It just sounds worse than it actually is. What do you think?
Yeah, you’re right. It’s technically not wrong.

Special.SourceString: Dumpster is fine. It is technically not wrong.

Text.SourceString: Yeah! It looks more like a place with some old stuff.

Special.SourceString: Dumpster does sound harsh. It looks nothing like it.

Text.SourceString: Unexpected, but fair. I like the way you think.

Special.SourceString: I need time to think. This is a matter of principle.

Text.SourceString: What’s up with people calling the recycling area the dumpster?
I guess it’s not wrong. It just sounds worse than it actually is.
I thought of turning my bonsai garden into a small fruit patch, but the only fruits I like are mangoes.
I suppose I could plant mango trees.//<portrait=sad>Hmm… It’d be a boring fruit patch with only one kind of fruit, though.
I thought of turning my bonsai garden into a small fruit patch, but the only fruits I like are mangoes.
I suppose I could plant mango trees.//<portrait=sad>Hmm… It’d be a boring fruit patch with only one kind of fruit, though.
I thought of turning my bonsai garden into a small fruit patch, but the only fruits I like are mangoes.
I suppose I could plant mango trees.//<portrait=sad>Hmm… It’d be a boring fruit patch with only one kind of fruit, though.
It may not be a bad idea to plant more banana trees. Sam’s never seems to have enough of them…//<portrait=annoyed>Bananas, not trees.
Of course… I’ll plant fruit trees when I have a larger garden. Don’t you worry!
It may not be a bad idea to plant more banana trees. Sam’s never seems to have enough of them…//<portrait=annoyed>Bananas, not trees.
Of course… I’ll plant fruit trees when I have a larger garden. Don’t you worry!
It may not be a bad idea to plant more banana trees. Sam’s never seems to have enough of them…//<portrait=annoyed>Bananas, not trees.
Of course… I’ll plant fruit trees when I have a larger garden. Don’t you worry!
When I move out, I’ll look for a place with a yard so I can bring my bonsai over.
Who knows, I might start planting a thing or two. I always thought it would be so fun to have a pumpkin patch in the Fall.
When I move out, I’ll look for a place with a yard so I can bring my bonsai over.
Who knows, I might start planting a thing or two. I always thought it would be so fun to have a pumpkin patch in the Fall.
I have a lot of work to catch up on.
As far as I know, the fig tree and juniper bonsai are the two most common bonsai trees…//<portrait=sad>Errr…
I’m not a bonsai expert, so don’t quote me on that.//<portrait=sad>I was just trying to make conversation.
But I’m pretty sure about what I said earlier.
Errr… You are literally in my way.
I’m not sure why you’re here, to be honest.
My one piece of advice for bonsai is don’t water them every day.//I’d find out the individual needs of each tree and then make sure to provide it…//That’s the safest way to do it.
Sorry if that’s boring. I just thought since you’re a farmer, you’d be into that kind of stuff.
And I’m generalizing now. Oh gosh. I’m sorry.
Umm…?
Umm… What?
There isn’t much nightlife around here like nightclubs or late-night karaoke bars.
Are you surprised?//<portrait=concerned>You probably knew that before moving here, didn’t you?
Sure… I like my job. I don’t have to see too many people.//<portrait=annoyed>That would be tiring.
Hmm… One thing about my brother, <NPCName>Theo</>, is he’s very artistic, just like Mom.//He sings and plays instruments.
Not me… I don’t sing or play anything.
I like to walk outside by myself when I’m stuck on something…//Work stuff, usually.
I don’t go too far from the house, though.//Usually just to the lake and back.
If I had to choose a favorite place, I’d say the library…//People usually leave you alone in there.
Plus, it’s quiet.
I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.
Today? Hmm… I had a banana this morning.
I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.
Today? Hmm… I ate a tomato this morning.
I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.
Today? Hmm… I had an artichoke today.
Kidding. I had some grapes.//<portrait=concerned>Why are you so interested in my diet, anyway?
I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.
We had some leftover grapes from Fall. So I just had some of those this morning.
Breakfast food? I like pancakes.//<portrait=sad>Umm…
So, you seem to like wearing boots, huh?
Errr… Never mind my poor attempt at conversation.//I feel awkward now.
I repot my bonsai every three to five years…but I think doing it every four years is fine too, I think//Keep in mind some faster-growing trees need to be repotted more often.
Repotting is easy if you have the right tool.//For bonsai, you need a special root rake to do that.//<portrait=sad>Umm… Yeah.
Hey…
I was offered an on-site position at my job, but I declined.//It could be a new experience, like living in a big city…//Finally be on my own, get a pet, maybe?
But no. I really don’t want to leave Coral Island unless I have to.
I can always travel if I want to get away for a little while.
I wonder if there’s a bonsai version of that tree by your farm.
The tree on the lookout… The one by the lighthouse? Doesn’t ring a bell?
I was on my way to the beach yesterday and ran into <NPCName>Dippa</>. I said hi, but they ignored me.
It’s been on my mind. I keep wondering if I did anything wrong.//Or they could have just been having a bad day, I guess. Hmm…
I don’t feel like talking right now.
Working from home is nice, because you can save money on commuting and put it in your savings instead.
My dad is nice enough to let me stay here rent free.
I usually stay at my friend’s villa on Mondays.//Only when she isn’t in town, that is.
You know, just to keep an eye on it.
Don’t tell anybody, but I think somebody else lives in that villa at the beach.//I have my suspicions.
I work remotely from home. So I don’t need to go out very often, which is perfect for me.
I guess I’m not the talkative type.
It’s hard for me to make small talk.//And it’s especially hard if the small talk needs to be non-bonsai related.
Living in a cabin in the middle of nowhere sounds great.
I don’t know why it never occurred to me to become a farmer like you.
Umm…
The library is nice and quiet.//You can read in peace for hours without anybody bothering you.
I need that kind of space in my life.
I like reading about bonsai and cacti in my spare time.
Umm… What do you want?
Hmm... People say I come across as off-putting sometimes.
I promise you, I’m not. I just don’t have anything to talk about.//<portrait=normal>Also, the things I could talk about for hours, I legally can’t discuss with anyone outside of my team. So…
I like living at home with Dad and <NPCName>Theo</>.//<portrait=normal>I just hope they don’t feel like I’m a burden or anything, ha ha ha.
Hmm…
Socket & Pan is a good store, but they can’t build computers yet.

I built my PC in Pokyo. I had to wait months for some parts ’cause there was a shortage.//It was worth it, though. Now when I play Resident Vile, my PC isn’t angry anymore… And the graphics look amazing.
I need to get this done before noon.
Don’t you have animals to tend to?

There are so many games. It makes it hard to leave my room. That’s where I work…and game, I guess.//Do you play? I haven’t beat all the Resident Vile series, but I’m taking my time… Just enjoying the story.
I also like retro games…not like old ones, but the ones with a nostalgic feeling.//My favorite genre has to be farming simulators. Can’t get enough of them… I might make one someday!
You should only water bonsai trees when the soil gets slightly dry, to avoid overwatering them.
Ah, am I talking about bonsai again?//We can talk about the weather if you want.
I went to Pokyo several times for a team meeting, and somebody told me to get a massage so I could relax.
That was rude.//It made me mad, and I wasn’t relaxed at all.
I work in security for a Pokyo-based company.//Cyber security...why are you asking?
Sorry, I can’t talk about my job too much.//My employer is very strict about it.
Game development isn’t as easy as it sounds. It’s much more fun than I thought it would be, though!
Uh-huh… I make games in my free time. I’ve made a couple of games, not a lot.
It’s amazing how wealthy some people are. I’ve been doing my job for a while, and I’m still not used to it.
I’ve said too much.
Oh, I just cracked my back! That felt good.//<portrait=concerned>I think I’ve been sitting down too long. I pulled an all-nighter last night until 4 am, doing some QA for my game.//So many bugs…
I prefer not to work on the weekend, but sometimes I have no choice.
I went to Pokyo several times for a team meeting, and somebody told me to get a massage so I could relax.
That was rude.//It made me mad, and I wasn’t relaxed at all.
I’ve been wanting to upgrade my PC, but gosh… The parts are so expensive.//Too much demand right now. It’s gonna have to wait.
It’s always nerve-racking to post my game updates…//I don’t know. I’m scared to look at the comments, I guess.//I’m scared people might hate it…or hate <Italic>me</> for it. I don’t know…
I know this is such a cliché, but I just love how full of life Spring is. It’s so nice to listen to the birds again.//Birds are cool… Yeah.
This might be just my imagination, but my bonsai look so happy today. Like they’re glad Winter is finally over.
Do you know how to make a Spring frittata? I think you need an egg and some vegetables. Hmm…
Spring makes me crave Spring frittata.
I’ll work tonight… I wanna enjoy Spring today.
I love seeing all the plants come back to life in Spring.
I’m gonna miss Spring.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m not looking forward to the hot Summer.
I saw a crab playing around in the garden this morning. I don’t know how it got there ’cause we’re pretty far from the beach.
I wanna spend my Summer napping indoors all day… Hmm…//Maybe I <Italic>should</> do that.
My PC’s fan was angry yesterday. <Italic>Mmm</>, <Italic>mmm</>, <Italic>mmm</> all day long.//The heat got to it too, I think.
We planted some lemongrass in the garden. It repels mosquitos.//Well, not “we,” actually. Mom did… She planted when…//Anyway, lemongrass really helped with the Summer bug situation.
Fall is a bummer in the house.//It wasn’t always like that… We used to make our own mooncakes. They weren’t as good as the ones from the Harvest Festival.//But making them was… It was cool.
There’s a corn maze at the Harvest Festival in another town nearby.//Yeah, went there a couple of times. It was kinda fun…//It’s fun here too. I like the pumpkin-smash game.
A few Falls ago, I volunteered to read scary stories at the school.//Never got an invitation to go back. I don’t really think they enjoyed it.
The cooler weather is nice.//It’s my favorite.
I think I’ll watch some old classics tonight after work… Like <Italic>Alakazam</> or <Italic>Shriek</>.
The Fall vibe is perfect for watching witchy horror films.
All my bonsai are temperate, so I don’t have to do too much to prepare them for Winter.//<portrait=concerned>Well, it’s still a lot of work, actually, but at least not as much as for tropical bonsai.
It’s kinda nice not to have to work outdoors in this weather.//My PC has angry fans as well, which is great to keep me warm.//Oh, not always… Only when I open certain things.

A cat broke into our home one night last Winter. It broke the window in the kitchen, stole some food, and left.//We woke up to a freezing cold kitchen. It took us the whole day to fix the window.//Oh, it was a cat, all right. There were hairs!
I heard there’ll be a lot of interesting booths at the Winter Fair. I wonder if it’s worth going when it’s this cold.
I think I’ll work on my game this Winter. More than usual.
Hmm… Do I want to make games full time? I don’t know. That sounds scary.//What if they don’t sell? I need a stable income.
The one good thing about Winter is I can wear hoodies every day, and no one judges me.
Pufferfish is an oil-drilling company.//From what I gathered, they’re looking to install some rigs offshore.
They’re prevented from doing it by the court until they legally get a majority vote on this island.
Pufferfish is moving its office here to buy property.//I hope nobody’s selling theirs. I’d hate to see Coral Island become an oil-drilling spot.
I’m bringing some coconut drinks to the Cherry Blossom Festival tomorrow.
<NPCName>Theo</> gets a stomachache every time he drinks milk. He hates it.
Yet he still eats cheese… Silly man.
Have you gotten anything from Socket & Pan yet?//They have good products.
Buying your Summer seeds yet, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I don’t stay at the villa during the Summer, because <NpcName>Nina</> is already here.//Besides, the beach gets really hot <Italic>really</> early in the morning anyway.
It’s too hot to use a blanket at night now.
It’s a problem, because I sleep better with it.
My mom was a high-spirited person. That’s why I’m so lively.
Kidding…
Are you attending the beach cleanup tomorrow?
Me too. See you there.
I see. I hope to see you there.
It’s my dad’s birthday today, so I’m making seafood ramen for dinner.
It’s his favorite…
I really don’t feel like chatting today, <PlayerName>$player</>. I hope you understand.
I’m so sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I really can’t talk right now.
My hoodie comes in handy in this weather.
I heard a really loud howl last night coming from your part of the island.
I wonder if it was your pet or <NPCName>Luke</>’s dog, <NPCName>Taco</>.
We lost Mom in the Fall, some years ago… It’s always the hardest season for <NPCName>Theo</> and me, but he wouldn’t admit it, ’cause he’s always so good at hiding his emotions.
I wish <NPCName>Theo</> wouldn’t hide his feelings and just let them out, ’cause if you strain something too long, it’ll eventually break… I don’t want my brother to break.
I’m NEVER taking my hoodie off.
Especially when it snows like this!
Hot cocoa sounds so good right now.
I have some jewelry made from jade. If you want to find some, watch out for treasure chests.//Sometimes there’s jade inside them.
No, I don’t think jade is natural in this area.
I have some jewelry made from jade. If you want to find some, watch out for treasure chests.//Sometimes there’s jade inside them.
No, I don’t think jade is natural in this area.
I tried to explain to my dad about a game concept I was developing, and I got a lecture about “real jobs” instead.
Bummer…
I’m just going to relax and enjoy the rain for a bit.
I’ll just work later.
One thing I like about this job is I can set my own hours.//I have the flexibility to do my own thing, like making games or playing them, which is cool.
I might just work tomorrow. The rain makes me feel a bit lazy.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t know… Maybe I’ll play some games instead. I have plenty of games in my Vapor account that I haven’t played.
One thing I like about this job is I can set my own hours.//I have the flexibility to do my own thing, like making games or playing them, which is cool.
The snow just keeps piling up.
Some of my bonsai are dropping leaves.
*brrrr*
I’m mostly here to support <NPCName>Theo</>.
Not usually a big fan of crowds…
Umm… Are you here to see me?
I rarely get any visitors.
*mumbles* It doesn’t work, and I don’t know why.
*mumbles* It worked perfectly before.
I use an alias for game development to keep my hobby separate from my job.
Sorry, can’t tell you. You’re just going to have to find out on your own.//<portrait=normal>But here’s one clue I can give you: you’ve been staring at it all along.
I really have to focus on this right now.
It’s nice of you to visit…
I work in the kitchen sometimes instead of just in my room.//I heard it’s important to change things up.
I’m glad I took the advice.
They’re small, but bonsai require a lot of care.
Focusing on gardening helps me organize my thoughts.
Ouch!
Watch your step, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Oops. Sorry!
Didn’t mean to step on your foot.
My brother caught a legendary fish here one time.
A flower horn, I believe. The one with a huge forehead and a somewhat rounded body.
Mom used to take <NPCName>Theo</> and me here to do our homework on our way back from school.
This is a bit far from your cabin, isn’t it?
Having a beach day, <PlayerName>$player</>?
It’s the perfect weather for diving, wouldn’t you agree?
It’s crazy to think sometimes that <NPCName>Suki</> has a young girl.
Maybe someday I could be a mom too.
Other than to my bonsai, that is.
This is nice, isn't it?//A nice, hot bath…the quiet Winter night. It's perfect.
